going to my place at this hour.

279
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:33,000
I might as well take the ferry
and then switch to the subway.

280
00:17:33,039 --> 00:17:35,000
That won't do.
Let me give you a ride.

281
00:17:36,170 --> 00:17:38,119
By the way,
why do you live so far away?

282
00:17:38,480 --> 00:17:40,559
You must spend a lot of time
commuting every day.

283
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:42,839
Mr. Zhou.

284
00:17:43,319 --> 00:17:45,759
That's easy for you to say,

285
00:17:46,170 --> 00:17:48,650
but I can't afford to rent
a place closer to the company.

286
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:49,758
That's easy.

287
00:17:49,759 --> 00:17:50,919
I'll rent it for you.

288
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:51,920
No.

289
00:17:52,359 --> 00:17:54,890
If I live in the house you rent,
I'll be like your kept woman.

290
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:56,000
I don't want that.

291
00:17:58,799 --> 00:17:59,920
Just drive...

292
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:01,759
and take me to the ferry terminal.

293
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,000
Yes, ma'am.

294
00:18:23,720 --> 00:18:24,799
Be careful on the road.

295
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:25,960
Text me when you get home.

296
00:18:26,599 --> 00:18:27,649
Don't worry.

297
00:18:27,650 --> 00:18:29,440
I take this route twice daily.

298
00:18:29,480 --> 00:18:30,559
It's not like
I'm going on an adventure.

299
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:32,439
Hurry up and go.
Parking isn't allowed here.

300
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:33,440
- All right.
- Bye.

301
00:18:33,441 --> 00:18:34,519
Bye.

302
00:19:12,170 --> 00:19:13,240
I'm a bad woman.

303
00:19:14,519 --> 00:19:16,519
A typical jerk.

304
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:18,519
Even Sun Han Han
thinks you're a jerk.

305
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,000
You're really a jerk.

306
00:19:21,319 --> 00:19:23,440
To be honest, aren't you happy?

307
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:29,720
A little.

308
00:19:31,079 --> 00:19:33,519
When they're fighting over me,

309
00:19:34,319 --> 00:19:36,440
it makes me feel like
they care about me.

310
00:19:38,279 --> 00:19:39,359
I'm quite happy.

311
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:40,799
You're incorrigible.

312
00:19:40,890 --> 00:19:43,319
Get your morals back in check...

313
00:19:43,559 --> 00:19:46,559
and put away
that darned sense of satisfaction.

314
00:19:52,410 --> 00:19:54,039
Qu Yi Peng
is not answering my calls.

315
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:56,719
Do you think he's ignoring me?

316
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:57,759
Serve you right.

317
00:19:58,240 --> 00:19:59,440
Don't worry.

318
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:01,799
Jealousy only makes men
love you more.

319
00:20:07,839 --> 00:20:08,920
- Qu Yi Peng?
- Gao Peng?

320
00:20:11,650 --> 00:20:12,838
You have to make it clear
to Gao Peng...

321
00:20:12,839 --> 00:20:13,920
before you see him.

322
00:20:49,480 --> 00:20:50,519
Boyfriend?

323
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:51,759
Ex-boyfriend.

324
00:20:52,559 --> 00:20:53,650
He has left.

325
00:20:56,170 --> 00:20:57,200
Did you lie to me?

326
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:06,960
Did he sleep
at your place last night?

327
00:21:07,680 --> 00:21:08,759
No.

328
00:21:09,319 --> 00:21:11,119
He had a fight with his parents
and had nowhere to go.

329
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:12,960
He slept on the couch.

330
00:21:13,759 --> 00:21:14,799
I swear.

331
00:21:18,799 --> 00:21:20,119
Why are you telling me this now?

332
00:21:20,759 --> 00:21:21,839
I don't want you to overthink it.

333
00:21:44,799 --> 00:21:45,799
Nan Nan.

334
00:21:49,039 --> 00:21:50,410
Do you have any expectations...

335
00:21:51,359 --> 00:21:52,599
for our future?

336
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:55,680
I don't know.

337
00:22:01,319 --> 00:22:02,400
What about you?

338
00:22:09,519 --> 00:22:10,720
I want us to get married.

339
00:22:15,559 --> 00:22:16,640
What do you think?

340
00:22:28,039 --> 00:22:29,160
Actually,

341
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:31,720
I don't have a clear idea...

342
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:33,200
about marriage.

343
00:22:34,599 --> 00:22:35,880
I'm not in a hurry either.

344
00:22:44,119 --> 00:22:45,599
But the word "marriage"...

345
00:22:47,319 --> 00:22:48,400
feels so sacred,

346
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:51,000
romantic,

347
00:22:53,799 --> 00:22:54,799
and blissful.

348
00:22:56,680 --> 00:22:57,920
It's like being acknowledged,

349
00:22:59,559 --> 00:23:01,119
loved,

350
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:03,559
and chosen by someone.

351
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:16,039
It's like earning
a certificate of love.

352
00:23:42,319 --> 00:23:44,200
Let's review
the key points from the last video.

353
00:23:44,319 --> 00:23:45,319
Many people...

354
00:23:45,599 --> 00:23:47,720
no longer believe
in the phrase "I love you".

355
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:49,758
They see it as
an expression of emotion...

356
00:23:49,759 --> 00:23:50,759
rather than a commitment.

357
00:23:51,079 --> 00:23:52,318
It has long become...

358
00:23:52,319 --> 00:23:54,279
the most clichÃ©d
and irresponsible phrase.

359
00:23:54,599 --> 00:23:57,079
It's merely a passionate declaration
without any responsibility.

360
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:58,480
Always keep in mind...

361
00:23:58,720 --> 00:23:59,959
that when interacting
with a partner,

362
00:23:59,960 --> 00:24:01,038
a meaningful confession...

363
00:24:01,039 --> 00:24:02,279
should be as fitting...

364
00:24:02,680 --> 00:24:04,240
and sincere as a commitment.

365
00:24:04,599 --> 00:24:05,920
"I want us to get married"
is different.

366
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:07,758
This phrase hasn't been overused.

367
00:24:07,759 --> 00:24:09,000
It's still full of ceremony...

368
00:24:09,160 --> 00:24:10,559
and the warmth of life,

369
00:24:10,799 --> 00:24:12,400
embodying the beauty
of walking hand in hand.

370
00:24:17,759 --> 00:24:21,880
(I'm currently trying...)

371
00:24:27,839 --> 00:24:28,880
Babe.

372
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:31,759
Babe.

373
00:24:37,839 --> 00:24:38,839
Gao Peng.

374
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:41,240
I wish I could speak
to you openly...

375
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:43,799
and honestly in person,

376
00:24:46,319 --> 00:24:48,000
but whenever the words
are on the tip of my tongue,

377
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:50,599
I can't seem to say them.

378
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:55,880
I'm currently trying
to start a new relationship.

379
00:24:58,279 --> 00:24:59,319
No matter what,

380
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:03,680
we've shared
a lot of wonderful moments...

381
00:25:05,480 --> 00:25:07,279
over the past seven years.

382
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:38,920
Nan Nan.

383
00:25:38,960 --> 00:25:40,000
Thank you.

384
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:41,479
If it weren't for you,

385
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:42,640
I really have no idea
what I would have done.

386
00:25:43,319 --> 00:25:44,440
- Gao Peng.
- Listen to me, Nan Nan.

387
00:25:44,599 --> 00:25:45,640
Listen to me.

388
00:25:46,079 --> 00:25:47,160
On my way home yesterday,

389
00:25:47,759 --> 00:25:48,920
I kept thinking
about what you said...

390
00:25:50,200 --> 00:25:51,358
to calm myself down.

391
00:25:51,359 --> 00:25:52,359
It's really effective.

392
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:54,640
Listening to them calmly
is actually not that hard.

393
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:56,240
You're right.

394
00:25:57,519 --> 00:25:59,799
I'm the one
who refused to communicate.

395
00:26:00,599 --> 00:26:02,160
I felt it for the first time...

396
00:26:02,799 --> 00:26:03,839
that my parents...

397
00:26:04,839 --> 00:26:05,880
are getting old.

398
00:26:07,920 --> 00:26:08,960
They need me...

399
00:26:10,160 --> 00:26:11,160
and anticipate my support.

400
00:26:11,559 --> 00:26:13,439
The way they want to speak,

401
00:26:13,440 --> 00:26:14,599
but are afraid of making mistakes...

402
00:26:15,759 --> 00:26:17,599
makes me feel uneasy and guilty.

403
00:26:19,559 --> 00:26:20,599
So I've decided.

404
00:26:21,240 --> 00:26:22,480
I'm going to Hong Kong tomorrow.

405
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:23,880
I'll gradually take over their work.

406
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:25,039
Don't worry.

407
00:26:31,839 --> 00:26:32,839
I've bought a lot of food.

408
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:35,679
This is pineapple.

409
00:26:35,680 --> 00:26:36,759
Seasonal pineapples.

410
00:26:37,319 --> 00:26:39,319
These are for Jojo.

411
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:41,200
And these little persimmons.

412
00:26:42,319 --> 00:26:43,720
And most importantly,

413
00:26:44,960 --> 00:26:45,960
this bottle of wine.

414
00:26:46,599 --> 00:26:47,680
We have to finish it.

415
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:49,720
These are chopsticks.

416
00:26:49,759 --> 00:26:51,039
There's a lot anyway.

417
00:26:51,559 --> 00:26:53,119
We'll go downstairs to buy more
after we finish these.

418
00:26:53,519 --> 00:26:55,359
- If you want anything...
- Gao Peng, we broke up.

419
00:27:03,799 --> 00:27:04,839
It's okay to break up.

420
00:27:05,519 --> 00:27:06,999
We broke up a few times before.

421
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:08,400
- Didn't we make up?
- It's different this time.

422
00:27:10,599 --> 00:27:11,640
We're not kids anymore.

423
00:27:12,799 --> 00:27:13,838
I'm serious.

424
00:27:13,839 --> 00:27:14,839
No.

425
00:27:15,160 --> 00:27:16,200
Don't do this, Nan Nan.

426
00:27:16,240 --> 00:27:17,240
Sit down.

427
00:27:18,279 --> 00:27:19,400
It was all my fault.

428
00:27:19,559 --> 00:27:20,598
I promise to change.

429
00:27:20,599 --> 00:27:22,039
Give me another chance, okay?

430
00:27:37,039 --> 00:27:38,079
This.

431
00:27:38,119 --> 00:27:39,199
Why are you going through my stuff?

432
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:40,200
I'm not.

433
00:27:40,319 --> 00:27:41,640
I bid it this morning...

434
00:27:41,880 --> 00:27:42,960
and chose to meet in person.

435
00:27:45,119 --> 00:27:48,720
When I saw you listing it
on the online marketplace,

436
00:27:48,920 --> 00:27:50,078
I was so angry.

437
00:27:50,079 --> 00:27:51,440
That's why I called you.

438
00:27:51,759 --> 00:27:53,640
But after I called you,
I regretted it.

439
00:27:54,039 --> 00:27:55,440
As you know,
I'm bad at coaxing people.

440
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:56,559
Especially over the phone.

441
00:27:57,119 --> 00:27:58,720
I was afraid I'd make things worse,

442
00:27:58,759 --> 00:28:00,559
so I thought
I should talk to you in person...

443
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:02,200
to clarify things
and ask for a reconciliation.

444
00:28:02,359 --> 00:28:04,039
Nan Nan, listen to me.

445
00:28:04,359 --> 00:28:05,758
Please listen to me.

446
00:28:05,759 --> 00:28:06,759
Listen to me.

447
00:28:07,079 --> 00:28:08,599
It's 49,999.

448
00:28:10,720 --> 00:28:11,759
I know.

449
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:13,720
You marked the price
so that I would buy it back.

450
00:28:18,039 --> 00:28:19,079
The first time...

451
00:28:22,240 --> 00:28:24,440
I saw you wearing it
seven years ago...

452
00:28:27,200 --> 00:28:28,279
feels like just yesterday.

453
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:35,200
I don't remember...

454
00:28:36,319 --> 00:28:38,240
the title or plot of that movie.

455
00:28:41,400 --> 00:28:42,640
Because at that time,

456
00:28:43,119 --> 00:28:44,319
I was only looking at you.

457
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:50,720
I remember you were crying...

458
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:52,640
with tears and snot all over.

459
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:29,240
What are you looking at?

460
00:29:34,720 --> 00:29:35,799
It's so spicy.

461
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:20,880
Come on.

462
00:30:22,599 --> 00:30:23,640
Let's go.

463
00:30:58,079 --> 00:31:01,480
(Jiangzhou Taxi)

464
00:31:22,799 --> 00:31:23,839
I still remember...

465
00:31:24,680 --> 00:31:25,680
how good we were,

466
00:31:27,680 --> 00:31:29,160
- If you...
- but it's in the past now.

467
00:31:29,319 --> 00:31:30,319
No.

468
00:31:31,680 --> 00:31:33,038
No. I'll go home now.

469
00:31:33,039 --> 00:31:34,039
- I'll tell my parents...
- Gao Peng.

470
00:31:34,039 --> 00:31:35,039
that I'm not going to Hong Kong.

471
00:31:35,040 --> 00:31:36,118
I'll leave after we reconcile.

472
00:31:36,119 --> 00:31:37,160
- Okay?
- Gao Peng.

473
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:39,919
Gao Peng, are you
throwing a tantrum again?

474
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:41,719
- I'm not.
- Yes, you are!

475
00:31:41,720 --> 00:31:42,798
You're the one who doesn't want
to go back to Hong Kong.

476
00:31:42,799 --> 00:31:43,838
Don't use me as an excuse.

477
00:31:43,839 --> 00:31:44,919
I didn't.

478
00:31:44,920 --> 00:31:47,440
I sincerely want
to start over with you.

479
00:31:47,559 --> 00:31:48,960
Sincerely?

480
00:31:53,559 --> 00:31:55,319
It's too late.

481
00:31:55,759 --> 00:31:56,839
How is it too late?

482
00:31:57,319 --> 00:31:59,359
How is it too late?
It's not too late.

483
00:32:00,359 --> 00:32:02,079
There's still
a cooling-off period for divorce.

484
00:32:02,240 --> 00:32:03,480
We can break up
if you really want to.

485
00:32:03,519 --> 00:32:04,759
Let's wait until
the cooling-off period is over.

486
00:32:05,119 --> 00:32:06,200
Right now,

487
00:32:06,599 --> 00:32:07,640
I'm very calm.

488
00:32:07,680 --> 00:32:08,680
You're not very calm.

489
00:32:08,681 --> 00:32:09,720
You're not.

490
00:32:13,799 --> 00:32:14,880
In three months and five days,

491
00:32:14,920 --> 00:32:16,400
it will be our seventh anniversary.

492
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:17,960
We agreed last year...

493
00:32:18,079 --> 00:32:19,440
that we'd celebrate it
in Hong Kong this year.

494
00:32:19,559 --> 00:32:20,640
Did you forget?

495
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:39,000
You didn't forget.

496
00:32:40,240 --> 00:32:41,279
Right?

497
00:32:43,839 --> 00:32:45,000
You didn't forget at all.

498
00:32:59,759 --> 00:33:03,999
(Seventh anniversary)

499
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:05,039
By the way,

500
00:33:05,519 --> 00:33:07,000
I've bought you
the ticket to Hong Kong.

501
00:33:07,559 --> 00:33:09,279
I've added it
to the list of reminders.

502
00:33:09,599 --> 00:33:10,880
Your phone will remind you.

503
00:33:12,720 --> 00:33:13,759
Nan Nan.

504
00:33:14,519 --> 00:33:15,720
Do you have any expectations...

505
00:33:16,319 --> 00:33:17,480
for our future?

506
00:33:19,559 --> 00:33:20,599
What about you?

507
00:33:21,279 --> 00:33:22,559
I want us to get married.

508
00:33:26,559 --> 00:33:29,319
One is a tall, handsome,
and dedicated scholar.

509
00:33:29,400 --> 00:33:31,440
The other
is a wealthy business elite.

510
00:33:31,880 --> 00:33:32,880
One is asking for marriage...

511
00:33:32,881 --> 00:33:33,920
and the other
is seeking reconciliation.

512
00:33:34,839 --> 00:33:35,839
This is too satisfying...

513
00:33:35,960 --> 00:33:37,359
and too sinful, isn't it?

514
00:33:38,079 --> 00:33:39,319
Don't you feel guilty?

515
00:33:41,119 --> 00:33:42,119
After we broke up,

516
00:33:42,519 --> 00:33:43,880
I didn't tell Gao Peng...

517
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:45,639
that I have a new boyfriend...

518
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:46,759
because I'm afraid he can't take it.

519
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:49,000
What would you like?

520
00:33:49,001 --> 00:33:50,039
Two bowls of noodles, please.

521
00:33:50,079 --> 00:33:51,160
Okay, two bowls of noodles.

522
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:52,279
Tell me the truth.

523
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:54,639
Are you leaving yourself
a way out...

524
00:33:54,640 --> 00:33:56,000
- by not being honest with Gao Peng?
- Your noodles.

525
00:33:56,920 --> 00:33:58,119
Here, your noodles are ready.

526
00:33:58,839 --> 00:34:00,480
I couldn't bring myself to tell him.

527
00:34:01,519 --> 00:34:03,839
I just couldn't make myself
send him the letter I wrote.

528
00:34:04,759 --> 00:34:06,880
I originally planned to wait
until he returns to Hong Kong...

529
00:34:06,960 --> 00:34:08,000
to talk to him about it slowly.

530
00:34:08,639 --> 00:34:10,769
I have to remind you
at this crucial moment.

531
00:34:11,159 --> 00:34:12,809
With Gao Peng's
current capabilities,

532
00:34:13,289 --> 00:34:15,880
he should be a very desirable match.

533
00:34:16,329 --> 00:34:17,769
I know.

534
00:34:19,679 --> 00:34:20,769
Do you really not love him anymore?

535
00:34:38,039 --> 00:34:39,119
Sometimes,

536
00:34:39,639 --> 00:34:40,679
I find myself feeling lost.

537
00:34:42,360 --> 00:34:43,920
I'm too familiar with him.

538
00:34:45,679 --> 00:34:46,719
The familiarity between us...

539
00:34:47,599 --> 00:34:48,960
can be exhausting,

540
00:34:49,039 --> 00:34:51,329
yet it also provides
a unique sense of security.

541
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:56,769
Anyway, when I'm with Qu Yi Peng,
it's a whole different experience.

542
00:34:59,119 --> 00:35:01,038
Are you in love with Qu Yi Peng...

543
00:35:01,039 --> 00:35:02,719
or is it just the excitement
of a new romance?

544
00:35:07,840 --> 00:35:08,840
It might be both.

545
00:35:08,920 --> 00:35:09,960
Can you really tell the difference?

546
00:35:10,679 --> 00:35:11,719
You're right.

547
00:35:15,289 --> 00:35:16,289
When you talked about Gao Peng,

548
00:35:16,400 --> 00:35:17,960
it reminded me of Zhou Bin
and his ex-wife.

549
00:35:18,519 --> 00:35:20,480
They must have developed
a familial bond.

550
00:35:21,039 --> 00:35:22,769
He said that's different from love.

551
00:35:23,199 --> 00:35:25,480
Our relationship is full of passion,

552
00:35:26,719 --> 00:35:28,159
but can passion last forever?

553
00:35:36,199 --> 00:35:37,289
I don't know.

554
00:36:22,679 --> 00:36:23,879
Why are you here?

555
00:36:23,880 --> 00:36:25,480
What? Am I not welcome?

556
00:36:25,599 --> 00:36:26,638
Come on in.

557
00:36:26,639 --> 00:36:27,639
Do I need to change my shoes?

558
00:36:27,640 --> 00:36:28,718
No.

559
00:36:28,719 --> 00:36:29,809
What happened to you?

560
00:36:31,039 --> 00:36:32,199
Didn't you drive?

561
00:36:32,519 --> 00:36:33,809
No, I took the subway.

562
00:36:35,329 --> 00:36:37,440
Didn't you tease me last time?

563
00:36:38,329 --> 00:36:40,599
I thought
I should really experience...

564
00:36:41,239 --> 00:36:42,440
what your daily commute is like.

565
00:36:46,480 --> 00:36:47,880
I haven't taken the subway
for years.

566
00:36:49,719 --> 00:36:51,639
When I entered the subway station,
I was like a headless chicken.

567
00:36:52,289 --> 00:36:53,480
I didn't even know
where to buy a ticket.

568
00:36:55,159 --> 00:36:56,329
After finally getting one,

569
00:36:57,599 --> 00:36:58,639
I got crammed into the subway...

570
00:36:59,440 --> 00:37:00,769
like a lightning bolt.

571
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:06,920
I even ended up
at the wrong station.

572
00:37:07,519 --> 00:37:09,599
When I exited the station,
I even went to the wrong exit.

573
00:37:10,440 --> 00:37:11,559
And just my luck,
it started raining.

574
00:37:14,239 --> 00:37:15,359
Hurry up
and drink some cold medicine.

575
00:37:15,360 --> 00:37:16,360
Don't catch a cold.

576
00:37:16,361 --> 00:37:17,400
Thank you.

577
00:37:18,809 --> 00:37:19,809
I counted.

578
00:37:20,599 --> 00:37:21,719
From your office to home,

579
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:22,880
there are 17 stops in total.

580
00:37:23,079 --> 00:37:24,079
You have to transfer three times...

581
00:37:24,920 --> 00:37:27,039
and it takes
a full hour and nine minutes.

582
00:37:30,769 --> 00:37:31,880
Your daily life...

583
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:33,480
is too tough.

584
00:37:36,079 --> 00:37:37,079
Mr. Zhou.

585
00:37:37,599 --> 00:37:39,840
You've just experienced
the hardships of the commoners...

586
00:37:39,960 --> 00:37:40,960
and you can't take it anymore.

587
00:37:42,719 --> 00:37:44,480
I already got used to it.

588
00:37:44,559 --> 00:37:45,638
With my headphones on,

589
00:37:45,639 --> 00:37:47,289
I can listen to audiobooks,
music, and lectures.

590
00:37:48,039 --> 00:37:49,239
Sometimes,
I even binge-watch dramas.

591
00:37:49,360 --> 00:37:50,519
Before I know it, time has flown by.

592
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:53,000
I guess I have a lot
to learn from you.

593
00:37:57,159 --> 00:37:58,559
I happen to be cooking.

594
00:37:58,840 --> 00:38:01,000
Do you want to eat something
before you go?

595
00:38:02,599 --> 00:38:03,639
It's my pleasure.

596
00:38:11,480 --> 00:38:12,920
- Thank you.
- Have some soup first.

597
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:22,440
They're just some simple dishes.

598
00:38:22,480 --> 00:38:23,519
What do you think?

599
00:38:24,159 --> 00:38:25,159
It's not bad.

600
00:38:25,880 --> 00:38:27,159
You usually eat
pretty light, don't you?

601
00:38:29,920 --> 00:38:30,920
By the way,

602
00:38:31,289 --> 00:38:33,000
about what I told you
at the ferry terminal,

603
00:38:33,039 --> 00:38:34,119
what do you think?

604
00:38:39,679 --> 00:38:40,679
I just want to rent...

605
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:43,119
a place near your office.

606
00:38:43,159 --> 00:38:44,159
That way,
it'll be convenient for you too.

607
00:38:44,679 --> 00:38:45,679
Don't worry.

608
00:38:46,079 --> 00:38:47,159
I'll take care of everything.

609
00:38:51,809 --> 00:38:53,920
Do you mean you'll pay for the rent?

610
00:38:54,159 --> 00:38:55,199
Of course.

611
00:38:56,360 --> 00:38:58,400
Is that house
considered yours or mine?

612
00:39:02,079 --> 00:39:03,079
You paid for the rent.

613
00:39:03,239 --> 00:39:04,480
Of course it's yours.

614
00:39:04,639 --> 00:39:05,719
If I stay there,

615
00:39:06,199 --> 00:39:07,519
naturally, I'll be yours.

616
00:39:09,329 --> 00:39:11,360
If I eat the food you cook,

617
00:39:11,809 --> 00:39:13,288
will I be yours too?

618
00:39:13,289 --> 00:39:14,360
Not necessarily.

619
00:39:17,289 --> 00:39:18,329
What I mean is,

620
00:39:18,360 --> 00:39:19,440
they're two different things.

621
00:39:20,329 --> 00:39:21,518
We're in a good relationship now.

622
00:39:21,519 --> 00:39:22,599
That's why you say so.

623
00:39:22,679 --> 00:39:24,119
If we don't get along in the future,

624
00:39:24,239 --> 00:39:25,960
do I have to move out immediately?

625
00:39:30,079 --> 00:39:31,079
To me,

626
00:39:31,559 --> 00:39:33,119
relationships are pure.

627
00:39:33,880 --> 00:39:35,769
I don't want to give up
my equality and freedom...

628
00:39:36,079 --> 00:39:37,719
just because
I'm living in your house.

629
00:39:38,880 --> 00:39:39,920
You're young,

630
00:39:40,960 --> 00:39:42,199
but you have a set of principles.

631
00:39:46,119 --> 00:39:47,880
If we fight in that house,

632
00:39:48,079 --> 00:39:49,289
would you leave or would I?

633
00:39:49,480 --> 00:39:50,519
Of course I'll leave.

634
00:39:52,599 --> 00:39:54,289
I just want you
to live a comfortable life.

635
00:39:55,400 --> 00:39:56,440
To be honest,

636
00:39:57,480 --> 00:39:59,079
I really can't bear to see
the woman I love...

637
00:39:59,840 --> 00:40:01,559
suffer and go through this hardship.

638
00:40:04,599 --> 00:40:05,880
All right. I get it.

639
00:40:06,769 --> 00:40:08,719
Your sincerity
is more than enough for me.

640
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:11,880
As for renting a house for me,

641
00:40:12,639 --> 00:40:13,920
I won't accept it.

642
00:41:09,960 --> 00:41:10,960
Good morning.

643
00:41:32,159 --> 00:41:33,159
Good morning.

644
00:41:35,769 --> 00:41:36,808
Good morning.

645
00:41:36,809 --> 00:41:37,809
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

646
00:41:38,289 --> 00:41:39,329
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

647
00:41:43,159 --> 00:41:44,239
Good morning.

648
00:41:52,079 --> 00:41:53,480
Ever since I found out
he's in Hong Kong,

649
00:41:54,679 --> 00:41:56,840
everything I've done
is to get close to him.

650
00:41:57,809 --> 00:41:59,039
Was it for revenge?

651
00:42:04,440 --> 00:42:05,519
Good morning.

652
00:42:06,639 --> 00:42:07,679
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

653
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:09,039
Molina.

654
00:42:09,079 --> 00:42:11,039
Dingbao just sent this to us.

655
00:42:11,809 --> 00:42:12,840
Okay, thank you.

656
00:42:13,679 --> 00:42:14,880
- Good morning.
- Good morning, Ms. Hu.

657
00:42:15,440 --> 00:42:17,329
I read your email on my way.

658
00:42:17,679 --> 00:42:19,329
It was sent at 3am.

659
00:42:19,559 --> 00:42:20,599
Don't you ever sleep?

660
00:42:20,769 --> 00:42:21,840
I got some sleep.

661
00:42:22,400 --> 00:42:23,880
I don't sleep much
since I was little.

662
00:42:24,079 --> 00:42:25,480
I'll be fine
after five to six hours of sleep.

663
00:42:26,360 --> 00:42:27,519
I really envy you.

664
00:42:28,079 --> 00:42:29,960
If I don't sleep
for at least eight hours,

665
00:42:30,239 --> 00:42:31,329
my brain doesn't want to function.

666
00:42:31,599 --> 00:42:32,679
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

667
00:42:32,880 --> 00:42:33,880
Good morning.

668
00:42:34,360 --> 00:42:35,439
I read your report.

669
00:42:35,440 --> 00:42:36,519
It's well done.

670
00:42:36,809 --> 00:42:38,239
It's comprehensive and clear.

671
00:42:39,119 --> 00:42:41,199
Looks like you've adapted faster
than I thought.

672
00:42:43,239 --> 00:42:44,289
Ms. Hu.

673
00:42:44,360 --> 00:42:47,039
Actually, you're a legend
at Jiangzhou Law Firm.

674
00:42:47,329 --> 00:42:48,329
You're exaggerating.

675
00:42:48,840 --> 00:42:49,920
Ryan.

676
00:42:49,960 --> 00:42:51,078
Dingbao just sent this to us.

677
00:42:51,079 --> 00:42:53,288
Get it done
and submit it to me by 5pm.

678
00:42:53,289 --> 00:42:54,289
Okay.

679
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:55,840
Really?

680
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:57,239
Even though you're only
three years older than me,

681
00:42:57,519 --> 00:42:58,559
you're already one...

682
00:42:58,599 --> 00:43:00,119
of the youngest partners
in this firm.

683
00:43:00,809 --> 00:43:02,360
One of the main reasons...

684
00:43:02,559 --> 00:43:03,598
I made an effort
to come to Hong Kong...

685
00:43:03,599 --> 00:43:04,639
is to work under you.

686
00:43:07,920 --> 00:43:08,920
Han Su.

687
00:43:09,400 --> 00:43:10,808
You're different
from the other girls...

688
00:43:10,809 --> 00:43:11,879
from the mainland.

689
00:43:11,880 --> 00:43:12,960
How so?

690
00:43:15,599 --> 00:43:17,289
They're all much more
reserved than you.

691
00:43:18,119 --> 00:43:19,360
You're smart and diligent,

692
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:21,039
but that doesn't really matter.

693
00:43:21,679 --> 00:43:23,159
Everyone here is just as capable.

694
00:43:23,880 --> 00:43:24,920
However,

695
00:43:26,079 --> 00:43:28,239
you don't know
how to hide your ambition.

696
00:43:33,329 --> 00:43:34,599
That suits me quite well.

697
00:43:37,840 --> 00:43:38,880
Keep it up.

698
00:43:39,199 --> 00:43:41,159
I believe you'll win
the Best Lawyer award this year.

699
00:43:41,719 --> 00:43:44,239
At that time, our charming
and elegant Mr. Sun Xu...

700
00:43:44,360 --> 00:43:45,960
will personally present
the award to you.

701
00:43:49,760 --> 00:43:50,760
Good morning.

702
00:43:54,679 --> 00:43:57,679
Does Mr. Sun usually come here
for meetings or work?

703
00:43:59,239 --> 00:44:01,400
He's the most senior partner
in the Asia-Pacific region.

704
00:44:01,519 --> 00:44:02,639
He rarely comes to the office.

705
00:44:03,159 --> 00:44:04,239
Usually,

706
00:44:05,239 --> 00:44:07,879
he'll give a speech
at the annual dinner...

707
00:44:07,880 --> 00:44:09,880
and also hands out bonuses
to everyone.

708
00:44:12,400 --> 00:44:13,440
Do you admire him?

709
00:44:17,280 --> 00:44:18,360
Keep it up.
